{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, potential predictors of reporting quality in GPT-generated abstracts were investigated which included the word count limit of the abstract, word length of the main report, type of intervention, number of outcome measures and the significance of the study outcome.",
    "The readability of the abstracts was evaluated as assessors identified the most comprehensible and clearly presented abstract for each RCT study, and the rate of \"hallucination\" in output generated by both ChatGPT 3.5 and 4 was also measured.",
    "Assessors were blinded to the abstract allocation, ensuring unbiased evaluation.",
    "The abstracts were exclusively generated by TH, who did not partake in the evaluation process.",
    "NA, PZK, TR, AM and MMG were involved in appraising the quality of abstracts."
  ]
}